 approach a vast range of educational issues including Special Educational Needs, emotional wellbeing, mental health, behaviour and classroom practice. EPs carry out a wide range of st</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">atutory and non-statutory work that helps to improve learning, developmental and welfare outcomes for all children and young people, but especially those within the most vulnerable situations. </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Fitness to Practise</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 24.7pt; padding-left:10.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">p</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">rincipal concerns </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">that the AEP woul</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">d like to express</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> to the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Health Select Committee </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">are around</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> the Fitness to Practise process.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Feedback we have received is that in some</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> cases i</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">nvestigations are not carried out thoroughly – even when evidence has been provided it is not always interrogated thoroughly before the case is sent to investigatory committee. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">For example </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">recently a case </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">went to the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> Investigatory Committee without the reg</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">istrant’s employer being asked to provide any evidence. </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 24.7pt; padding-left:10.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">We would like to bring to the committee’s attention that a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> l</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ack of proper collection of relevant information at a very early stage can lead to registrants being referred to a full Investigatory Committee when the issue relates to a difference in professional opinion rather than any poor practice </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">issues</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Registrants</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> are put under high levels of unnecessary anxiety and registrants’ representatives have to expend much effort and time into dealing with matters (incurring a high level of unnecessary costs) because of inefficient and incomplete investigations. </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 24.7pt; padding-left:10.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">In our ex</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">perience </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Fitness to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">P</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ractise issues are dealt with inconsistently – it appears that different members of the Fitness to Practise team interpret the HCPC guidance differently so that registrants are treated differently from each other dependent upon which m</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">embers of staff is dealing with the particular case – this can become even more confusing for registrants and their representatives if telephone queries are dealt with by different HCPC staff.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="fo